Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor), but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Findings suggest possible diabetic nephropathy or another form of renal dysfunction with impaired concentrating ability. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
